org.dyn4j

Class BinarySearchTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dyn4j.BinarySearchTree<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Comparable
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SweepLine.EdgeBinaryTree

    public class BinarySearchTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Represents an Binary Search Tree.

    Null elements are not allowed and duplicates can have unexpected behavior.

    Use the isSelfBalancing() and setSelfBalancing(boolean) methods to make the tree an AVL tree.

    Since:
    2.2.0
    Version:
    3.0.2
    Author:
    William Bittle

        protected boolean insert(BinarySearchTree.Node item,
             BinarySearchTree.Node node)
